# Ship — Build and Deploy Features

Implement a new feature or enhancement from start to production. Balanced speed.

## Workflow Pipeline

```
Shipper ──► Full Stack Dev + DB Admin (parallel) ──► Shipper ──► Reviewer ──► Shipper ──► Documentor ──► Shipper
Branch       Implement feature                       Commit       Review       Test         Update Docs    Deploy+PR
```

## Steps

| # | Task | Role | Blocked By |
|---|------|------|------------|
| 1 | Create feature branch `feature/<name>` from main | Shipper | — |
| 2 | Implement the feature end-to-end | Full Stack Dev | 1 |
| 3 | Implement database/data layer changes (if needed) | DB Admin | 1 |
| 4 | Commit all changes with conventional message (`feat: ...`) | Shipper | 2, 3 |
| 5 | Review implementation for security, bugs, performance | Reviewer | 4 |
| 6 | Run full test suite | Shipper | 5 |
| 7 | Fix regressions (if tests fail — loop back to 6) | Full Stack Dev | 6 |
| 8 | Update documentation for feature changes | Documentor | 6 |
| 9 | Deploy and create PR to main | Shipper | 6, 8 |

## Key Points

- Steps 2 and 3 can run in parallel
- If step 6 finds failures, step 7 fixes them and loops back to 6
- Reviewer only blocks for CRITICAL security issues
- Documentation updates happen in parallel with final deployment prep
